DTSTAMP:20260325T091952Z
DTSTART:20260330T223000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, March 30\, 2026\, 3:30 - 5:30pm\n\nHomework Help volun
	teers will be at this branch to assist K-12 students with school assignmen
	ts during the school year.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nNorthgate Branch\n\nRoom L
	ocation: Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not requir
	ed.\n\nDetailed Description: If you are working on a tough homework assign
	ment or have questions about a lesson\, come to the Library for Homework H
	elp. We have volunteers who can help with math\, English\, social studies 
	and science.\, Students without homework can read and play learning enrich
	ment games with trained tutors.\, Snacks are provided at every Homework He
	lp: Thanks to the donors of\n\nThe Seattle Public Library Foundation\n\nfo
	r sponsoring this event.\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\n\, Registration is not req
	uired but these programs are very popular and the room capacity can fill u
	p quickly.\, While Homework Help is available to students from kindergarte
	n through 12th grade\, volunteers are not responsible for children\, who s
	hould not be left unsupervised.\,\n\nFind out more about Homework Help.\n\
	nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call
	 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for pe
	ople with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat leas
	t seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library pro
	grams are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/eve
	nts/#/details/homework-help/17650270/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts
	 & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/homework-help/17650270/20
	26-03-30T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
